j9jo3.9.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:21.234416463Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":339,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: E2E coverage must include long-lived filtered watch scenarios, healthy idle windows with heartbeats, replay-to-live handoff, heartbeat loss or liveness timeout, selector mismatch or unsupported-filter handling, and diagnostics that explain why a consumer saw silence.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:05Z"},{"id":346,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical operator-loop follow-up: end-to-end tests must cover an incident opening, a later operator asking for recent as-of context, replay-to-live comparison, restart and reconnect behavior, and verbose logs that make it obvious why ntm answered with reconstructed, cached, partial, or unavailable history.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:15Z"},{"id":357,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: end-to-end scenarios must include intentionally secret-bearing pane output, mail, and diagnostic evidence so the harness can prove redaction and disclosure behavior under real operator loops with detailed artifact logs.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:25Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","title":"robot-redesign/validation: refresh robot API docs, attention contract, and redesign transition notes","description":"Refresh the human-facing documentation so the new robot model, surface taxonomy, schemas, example payloads, attention semantics, explainability flows, and redesign transition story are documented in the repository rather than only in bead descriptions or institutional memory.","design":"The work should update the robot API docs, attention-feed contract docs, and redesign transition notes to explain the operator loop, schema versioning, freshness and degraded-state semantics, request identity and retry safety, attention aggregation, cooldown, resurfacing, operator acknowledgment or snooze or pin or escalation semantics, explainability and diagnostics flows, example payload corpus, deterministic test entry points, and the relationship between CLI and server transports. The docs should point future contributors to the checked-in examples and validation suites that define expected behavior, and they should explain what legacy paths were removed or replaced rather than implying long-lived compatibility scaffolding. The docs should describe the product as it is after the redesign, not preserve pre-redesign confusion for nostalgia.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when a contributor can understand and safely extend the redesign from repository docs, checked-in examples, and documented test entry points alone, including how request correlation, safe retries, compact attention semantics, and durable operator overrides are supposed to work, without needing the planning conversation that produced it.","notes":"This bead is the explicit answer to 'future self should not need the original markdown plan.'","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:29.470416826Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T19:59:44.662372128Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["docs","robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:36.544852874Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:54.354380181Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:02.115056405Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.13","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:02.045665014Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:20.765514180Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:21.800660511Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:27.063433078Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:55.560120013Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:45.659703716Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:06.296480488Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:11.191038422Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_