 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add unit tests for contracts, schema examples, and registry discovery logic","description":"Add focused package-local unit tests for the contract layer and discovery layer so the robot model stays explicit and machine-consumable. This task exists because schema/versioning rules, example payloads, surface metadata, and discovery output are easy to erode if only exercised indirectly by broader tests.","design":"The tests should cover schema ID and versioning rules, required or optional or empty field semantics, deterministic ordering requirements, normative example payload validation, truncation and pagination metadata semantics, action-handoff and remediation-hint shapes, request identity or idempotency rules, operator attention-state rules, recoverable error semantics, explainability and evidence shapes, aggregation or suppression metadata semantics, diagnostic discovery output, scenario or example drift detection, capabilities/help/schema discovery output, replacement or removal markers where relevant, and registry metadata consistency. They should be table-driven, live beside the implementation in _test.go files, and log scenario names, schema IDs, section names, request or outcome IDs, operator-state markers, suppression markers, error codes, diagnostic handles, and high-signal diffs when assertions fail.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when contracts, checked-in examples, and registry or discovery logic have deterministic unit coverage for happy-path, edge-case, and error-case behavior with detailed logging suitable for debugging drift quickly, including retry-safe, attention-hygiene, and operator-override semantics.","notes":"If a future contract change can silently alter discovery or field semantics without a noisy unit-test failure, this task is incomplete.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:47.707037882Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:02.136198527Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","unit","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:37.711187789Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:55.740778634Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:02.918437821Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.13","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:02.875563116Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:21.600327057Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:06.159581992Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:27.631778080Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:40.381104360Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:28.865968237Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:56.898464768Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.2","type":"blocks","crea