 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add unit tests for snapshot/status/digest/attention/inspect assembly and renderer projections","description":"Add focused package-local unit tests for the robot surfaces themselves so section assembly and renderer semantics stay stable. This task exists because user-facing breakage often happens where normalized state is turned into actual outputs, and that layer deserves direct verification in addition to goldens and E2E coverage.","design":"The tests should cover snapshot, status, digest, attention, inspect, and diagnostics assembly; section presence and omission rules; empty-array semantics; next_actions and remediation hints; request or outcome correlation handles; operator attention-state markers; inspect lookup behavior; invalid-target error handling; renderer omission signaling; truncation or pagination cues; aggregation or suppression cues; JSON, TOON, markdown, and terse projection rules; payload-budget markers where applicable; explanation handles and evidence summaries where the contract exposes them; and deterministic ordering. They should use the shared fixture corpus and log surface name, schema ID, scenario name, render format, changed sections, payload sizes, request or outcome IDs, operator-state markers, suppression markers, error codes, diagnostic handles, and field-level or textual diffs that explain failures clearly.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the robot surface assembly and renderer logic are pinned by unit tests that catch semantic drift early and produce rich debugging output when outputs change, including for safe retries, correlated outcomes, compact attention presentation, and durable operator control.","notes":"The point is to test semantics, not just serializer mechanics. Every assertion should make it easier to understand what user-visible behavior changed.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:50.114187103Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:36.652020806Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","unit","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:38.834299050Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:56.960386220Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:11.345682655Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:28.232492384Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:40.991860418Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:58.163835603Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:38.947646268Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:47.524049642Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:08.551321898Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:11.979564273Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9j